Date: 31 Aug 2000
From: Marjorie P. Pollack, M.D. <pollack@mindspring.co.>
Source: Blethen Maine News Service, 31 Aug 2000 [edited

Maine State to initiate testing of dead birds for West Nile virus
-----------------------------------------------------------------
Scientists at Maine's Health Laboratory have issued a public appeal for
dead birds from around the state so they can test them for the West Nile
virus, which has plagued New York and moved as far north as New Hampshire.
State health officials have established a 24-hour, toll-free hot line,
(888) 697-5846, to accept reports of dead birds, particularly crows.
Fortunately, temperatures in Maine will drop soon and mosquito activity
will all but cease, so even a positive finding would hold little threat for
humans.
[Byline: Gary J. Remal
